WEBVTT

00:04.712 --> 00:05.811
- You got the money?
- No.

00:05.879 --> 00:07.970
Then there's your answer.
But, Maya, come on.

00:07.971 --> 00:10.049
You thought you could skip
school to come ask me this?

00:10.073 --> 00:12.941
I got first period study hall.
I'm not missing anything.

00:13.010 --> 00:14.376
My partner's real by-the-book.

00:14.444 --> 00:16.923
You better get your ass to class
before she give you a summons.

00:16.947 --> 00:17.947
Well, whatever.

00:20.117 --> 00:22.851
Who's that?
Will, my little brother.

00:22.920 --> 00:26.221
Wouldn't buy him tickets
to some concert.

00:26.290 --> 00:27.689
The basketball player?

00:27.758 --> 00:29.357
Smelled like sweaty
gym bags, didn't he?

00:29.426 --> 00:32.794
A little. Looks like -
a good kid, though.

00:32.863 --> 00:34.930
He is.
I mean, they all are.

00:34.998 --> 00:36.531
What is it, three
younger siblings?

00:36.600 --> 00:39.000
And my mom, who's
more work than all of 'em.

00:39.069 --> 00:41.670
That sounds
like a handful.

00:41.738 --> 00:44.973
It's worth it
for the most part.

00:45.042 --> 00:48.910
Do you feel any remorse
for your actions, Dr. Peterson?

00:48.979 --> 00:49.911
None.

00:49.980 --> 00:52.347
None? Your daughter's dead.

00:52.416 --> 00:54.249
And I was trying to save her.

00:54.318 --> 00:57.319
The drugs you gave her caused
her to go into cardiac arrest.

00:57.387 --> 00:59.754
She had an idiopathic
autoimmune disorder.

00:59.823 --> 01:02.290
She was degenerating
and in pain.

01:02.359 --> 01:03.592
Risk was necessary.

01:03.660 --> 01:06.595
And did her actual doctors agree
with your assessment?

01:06.663 --> 01:08.463
Her doctors had been
trying and failing

01:08.532 --> 01:10.131
to diagnose her for years.

01:10.200 --> 01:11.477
They didn't know what
they were doing.

01:11.501 --> 01:14.102
My client doesn't mean to say
her doctors were incapable.

01:14.171 --> 01:15.503
Yes, I do.

01:15.572 --> 01:16.805
Just that with
his extensive

01:16.874 --> 01:18.540
credentials and experience...

01:18.609 --> 01:20.308
What I mean to say is,

01:20.377 --> 01:24.346
if anyone had a shot at saving
Sarah, it was me.

01:24.414 --> 01:26.715
What was I supposed to do?
Sit by and watch?

01:26.783 --> 01:30.285
Your attempt to cure her
led directly to her death.

01:30.354 --> 01:33.521
I feel... no remorse

01:33.590 --> 01:36.258
because I know that I did
everything I could,

01:36.326 --> 01:44.466
down to Sarah's
last minute on this earth.

01:51.575 --> 01:54.009
Looks like Ty's back
on his corner.

01:54.077 --> 01:55.577
Man, this dude
has got to be

01:55.646 --> 01:56.846
the world's worst drug dealer.

02:03.387 --> 02:05.120
Hands where I can see 'em.

02:05.188 --> 02:06.888
Didn't we just arrest
you a month ago?

02:06.957 --> 02:08.323
And between you and me,

02:08.392 --> 02:10.068
you're my favorite
arresting officers ever.

02:10.092 --> 02:11.804
All right, you know the drill.
Do you got any needles

02:11.828 --> 02:13.273
or anything sharp
that's gonna hurt me?

02:13.297 --> 02:14.496
No. I wouldn't hurt a fly.

02:14.564 --> 02:18.566
Ooh... looks like
we're taking a ride.

02:18.635 --> 02:20.235
Okay, okay, wait! Wait!

02:20.304 --> 02:22.070
I got information for you.
Oh, really?

02:22.139 --> 02:23.905
You got a dirty cop
in your precinct.

02:23.974 --> 02:25.373
Dirty how?

02:25.442 --> 02:26.586
Five-O has been arresting
a lot of people

02:26.610 --> 02:27.842
in Elmore's Complex, right?

02:27.911 --> 02:29.244
- Uh-huh.
- Word is,

02:29.313 --> 02:30.712
some cop's been taking
more money

02:30.781 --> 02:32.247
than you've been bragging about.

02:32.316 --> 02:35.450
You're saying a cop is taking
money from crime scenes?

02:35.519 --> 02:37.686
- Exactly.
- Get the hell in the car.

